# Booking Links

Per-account URLs the reply agent inserts into `{booking_url}` substitutions.
The agent picks the URL based on `account_key` at send time.

## Primary booking URLs (REQUIRED for auto-send-on-interested path)

{{#each booking_links}}
### {{persona_name}} — {{account_key}}

```yaml
account_key: {{account_key}}
persona: {{persona_slug}}
booking_url: {{url}}
```

{{/each}}

## UTM tracking rule (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Every booking URL the agent inserts into a reply MUST carry `?utm_source=bison` in the query string.
This is the attribution channel for replies the agent generates.

If a URL is updated without `utm_source=bison`, the build script will fail loudly.

## Known URL history

These URLs are canonical for this tenant and should not change without a new deployment.

{{#each booking_links}}
- {{url}} ({{persona_name}}, {{account_key}})
{{/each}}

## Hard rule (auto-send safety)

If any booking URL above is still `TODO_*_URL`, the auto-send path will NOT fire for that persona.
The agent will fall back to review-first (you approve in Telegram).

Once all real URLs are in place, auto-send unlocks.
